# Pizza Sales Analysis

#Project Overview
This Power BI dashboard analyzes a year, worth of pizza sales data to uncover key insights into customer preferences, peak sales periods, and revenue drivers.
It provides a high-level overview of sales performance to help optimize inventory and marketing strategies.

#Tool Used
Power BI

#KPI
Total Revenue: $817.86K.
Total Orders: 21.35K.
Average Order Value (AOV): $38.31.
Total Pizzas Sold: 49.57K.
Average Pizzas Per Order: 2.32.


#How to view this project:
Download the .pbix file from this folder.
Open it using Power BI Desktop.



#insights
Peak Volume: Friday evenings generate the highest revenue (~$136K), suggesting a need for increased staffing.
Customer Choice: The "Classic" category leads in sales volume, while "Large" pizzas account for nearly half of all sales.
Seasonality: Sales remained relatively stable throughout the year, with a slight dip in the latter months.
The Thai Chicken Pizza is the no.1 bestseller, contributing $43.43K in revenue.
Customer Favorites: Following closely are the Barbecue Chicken ($42.77K) and California Chicken ($41.41K), showing a strong consumer preference for chicken-based pizzas.
Menu Optimization: Identified the Brie Carre Pizza as a lower-tier performer in the top 5 ($11.59K revenue), highlighting potential areas for menu review or targeted promotion.
Volume vs. Value: While the Classic Deluxe has lower total revenue than the Thai Chicken, it maintains high order frequency, suggesting it is a staple "volume" item for the business.
